data.title: Birthday celebration
data.text: Went in July with family for birthday. Walked in the door and was hit with a horrible foul smell of drain problem. Left immediately after aloof hostess shrugged her shoulders when informed. I emailed corporate next day and got apology and gift certificate. Went back for lunch the next week and was treated very nicely and had very good lunch.

data.title: Weekday dinner was empty but service was poor
data.text: On a weekday the music was too loud and inappropriate, the mash potatoes was poorly done in chunks and not process correctly. The N.Y. Strip Steak was NOT done as ordered. The house salad was not impressive compare to McDonald's, theirs is better. This salad lacks carrots and cucumbers. The waitress was away too long and did not follow through with the needed water. The dessert selections was poor.

data.title: Horrible service and chef was asleep
data.text: We went on a Friday night expecting the decent meal and what we got was the worst nightmare out.  We always call ahead knowing the long wait.  We waited 20 minutes when we arrived which was expected, but then when we sat down the waiter didn't come over for another 15 minutes.  He took our drink orders and appetizer order.  The appetizer came out in 10 minutes, waiter didn't bring our drinks for 15 more minutes after our appetizers were gone.  Then he wasn't going to take our entree order till I told him.  Finally takes the order we continue to wait.  A family I know get seated, get their order taken by the same waiter.  Get their food.  We are still waiting.  45 minutes go by finally I flag down the manager who I apparently interrupted in her conversation with friends.  Our food comes out.  Cold, overcooked, and veggies were raw.  My daughter ordered medium rare.  Her steak is pictured.  It was well done.  2 hours wasted and 125 dollars.  When I complain about the wait, and service nothing gets done.  This place will be crossed off my list.  It's too bad too their giving Longhorn a bad name!

data.title: SO DELICIOUS!
data.text: We have eaten at this location multiple times and the food and service have been consistently great.  All eight of us were thoroughly happy with our meals.  We had ribs, grilled chicken, rib eye steak, salads, salmon, shaved prime rib and a  cheeseburger.  I had a Caesar salad and half a shaved prime rib sandwich ~  both excellent!  Service was most friendly and attentive.  This location is a winner!

data.title: One of best steaks I've had in a long time
data.text: We came here at around 5pm. The waitress was very nice and attentive. We all got steaks : T-bone, strip steak, and definitely try Flos filet, it was delicious. We got the crab balls which were delicious. Also , if you get a drink during happy hour , you get 2 for 1. The price is right as well you won't break the bank. This was by far the best place to eat since I've been down to visit.

data.title: Dinner
data.text: This is a great place to eat with more than just steaks.every thing is great. The appetizers are great  all the side dishes are very good. They have the best key lime pie in palm beach co.

data.title: Dinner
data.text: The food is excellent.  The waiter very excellent. Clean restaurant,  wash room was also very clean. Waiter was very good. Service very good.

data.title: Good for More than Just Steaks
data.text: We were a group of five when we visited the  Boynton Beach LongHorn Steakhouse last week. Three of us wanted to eat something other than steak. I combined the shrimp and lobster chowder (rich and delicious) with the Blue Ridge Wedge Salad (blue cheese and bacon crumbles and tomato bits over romaine lettuce). My neighbor combined the chowder  with a Strawberry & Pecan Salad which he reported was delicious. Our third non-steak eater combined a tempting onion soup with Brew Pub Pretzel Sticks which came with an interesting dipping sauce. We all reported complete satisfaction with our non-traditional choices.  I'd do it all over again.

data.title: Great food
data.text: The food was very good and the service was outstanding. Had a very nice family atmosphere. Good parking and didn't have any problem.

data.title: Saturday night dinner
data.text: Reasonably priced and the service is very good. Fantastic selection on the menu and the food is always tasty. I definitely recommend

data.title: A reasonable steakhouse? Here it is
data.text: The food has always been consistent and good. This is not a top steakhouse, but not bad at all, and affordable. The service, thus far, has always been good. The servers have always been very attentive and helpful.

data.title: Needs Refresh
data.text: Not crowded but long wait for service. A waitress from another table took our drink order because our waitress just never came.After she did come to take our order we didn't see her again until we were almost finished. It is obvious that management is cutting costs at the expense of the customer. This restaurant needs a big refresh with new menu items, updated decor and more staff training. We have eaten here many times over the years and the difference is very noticeable.

data.title: Long Wait Time
data.text:
But we avoided the one hour wait at 7pm by sitting at the bar. 
My 6oz filet was slightly over cooked, but it was still tasty. Very lean. My wife had the small prime rib cooked to a perfect medium rare. Both sides were generous portions; broccoli for her and a creamed spinach for me. 
Salads were decent, and house wine was $6.79 a glass (strict pour). They did offer bottles and a slightly larger pour.

data.title: About what you would expect.
data.text: We went there for lunch and they had an ok menu that had enough choices. The food was average the service was good.

data.title: Always crowded - good sign!
data.text: I love going to the Longhorn, typically for a girlfriend's night out.  The menu is substantial and the prices reasonable.   Usually there is a wait, but it is worth it!

data.title: Good meal but issues with coupon
data.text: We eat here and at other Longhorn restaurants frequently.  Came in this visit with a coupon for a free appetizer.  Server did not know how to handle it and and to wait for her manager to approve it.  After waiting over 10 minutes for the manager to come to the table to view the coupon on my phone, I got a bit upset with the server and let her know this.  Finally she just tok the amount off the check.  management really needs to address this issue.  If they want to discourage the use of the coupons, just put up a sign at the entrance.  If not, allow the servers to process them and patrons to leave after finishing their meals.

data.title: Consistent in both Food And Service!
data.text: Longhorn has never disappointed me. I was surprised at the not very nice reviews that I found when I was searching this location because we are on vacation in this area from Maine! But because I am a firm believer in the Longhorn chain, off we went! My husband and I were NOT disappointed! The prime rib was cooked to perfection, along with the loaded baked potato and asparagus as well as my lighter portion chicken fingers, mashed potatoes, and salad. Our waiter, Adam R., was awesome! Attentive to detail and some humorous stories to boot! The restaurant was clean and we were checked on several times by the young lady that I believe was the manager. We had a delightful time as we always do at Longhorn!

data.title: Great Steaks, service leaves a lot to be desired
data.text: Went solo for dinner on 4-6-16, after waiting 10 minutes with no one even acknowledging me, one of the other waitresses (Nicole) came by, took my order and apologized for the waiter, which he came 3 minutes later, he I felt was aloof and although he apologized, I kept seeing the same treatment to other people in his section, the Salad, Steak, and Fries were outstanding, however Service is a big part of any restaurant, and the service by the waiter assigned to my table, sucked while Nicole did a great job of salvaging the rating from a 1 star to a 3 star, I of course tipped Nicole and left NO TIP for the waiter in question

data.title: Excellent steaks
data.text: Went for dinner on a Saturday evening. The wait was around 20 min. as stated.  Had an excellent bloody Caesar.  Our order consisted of 2 Flo filets 6 oz. with salad & bake potato which was a perfect choice.  The steaks were one of the best I have ever eaten, so tender, I could have cut with a fork, and very reasonably priced.  Everything was excellent from the Caesar to the steaks & service.  Excellent choice of dining experience!

data.title: Enj
data.text: We visited with friends local in the area (Me and my boyfriend are from England) we had a 20 minute wait for the table, which was fine as it was super busy in the restaurant. We ordered a large array of starters including chilli cheese fries, kettle chips, corn fritters and and chicken bites, these were all tasty and went down a treat. For mains we all ordered the sirloin steaks with fries. I ordered mine medium rare, and it came medium rare. The steak was really tasty, it wasn't tough and really wasn't too fatty. We skipped on desserts as we were so full, we look forward to returning!
